item.title: My Presence on the Internet
item.description: Back in the early days of my bachelor’s degree, a friend of mine started a technical blog called The Code Note. I thought it was the coolest thing ever. Inspired, I decided to start my own blog. I spent days brainstorming a name (which, honestly, I can’t even remember now) and finally launched it. It was your typical “how to solve LeetCode problems” blog. Yeah, I know—there are already millions of those out there. But hey, it got me started.
